<tr><td></td><td>TEASER</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Settlement</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk, Spock, McCoy, Scott, Chekov and Galway beam down to a group of pre-fabricated buildings. The sky is orange.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>KIRK:  Where is everyone?</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Perhaps they weren't expecting us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Our arrival was scheduled well in advance, Doctor. The annual check of every scientific expedition is routine.</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KIRK:  I had a subspace contact with a Robert Johnson, the leader of this expedition, an hour ago.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Did he report anything wrong?</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>KIRK:  No, yet there was something wrong. I can't pin it down. His conversation was disjointed, his thoughts a little foggy, unrelated. Chekov, check that building. Mister Spock and I will check this one. The rest of you, take a look around. See if you can find anyone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Chekov goes into the dark building - it has no windows - and the light comes on as he bumps up against a table bearing the body of a very old man. He panics and runs out again.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>CHEKOV:  Captain! Captain! Captain! Captain!</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>KIRK:  What is it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>CHEKOV:  A man, sir. In there. A dead man.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Building</td></tr>
<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Again, the lights only come on when the party reaches the table in the middle of the room.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well?</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Exactly what it looks like. Death by natural causes. Old age.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Quite impossible, Doctor. I ran a personnel check on this expedition before we beamed down. I assure you that none of them were</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>(He is interrupted by the entrance of an old man and woman. ROBERT:  (to the woman) They've come to pay their respects to Alvin.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>KIRK:  I'm Captain Kirk of</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>ROBERT:  You'll have to speak louder.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>KIRK:  I say I'm Captain Kirk of the USS Enterprise. Who are you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>ROBERT:  I'm Robert Johnson. This is my wife, Elaine.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>KIRK:  How old are you? How old are you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>ROBERT:  I'm, er, let me see. I am twenty nine, and Elaine is</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>ELAINE:  I'm twenty seven.</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 3478.2. On a routine mission to re-supply the experimental colony at Gamma Hydra Four, we discovered a most unusual phenomenon. Of the six members of the colony, none of whom were over thirty, we found four had died and two were dying of old age.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Johnson, can you hear me?</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>ROBERT:  I can hear you. Not deaf yet, you know. Not yet.</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>KIRK:  Can you tell me what happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>ROBERT:  What happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>KIRK:  Did your instruments show anything?</td></tr>

<tr id="L30"><td><a href="#L30">30</a></td><td>ROBERT:  Elaine was so beautiful. So beautiful. So beautiful.</td></tr>

<tr id="L31"><td><a href="#L31">31</a></td><td>MCCOY:  He can hear you, Jim, but he doesn't understand. Let's let him rest.</td></tr>

<tr id="L32"><td><a href="#L32">32</a></td><td>KIRK:  (to nurse) If they seem lucid, I'll be in the briefing room.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Briefing room</td></tr>
<tr id="L33"><td><a href="#L33">33</a></td><td>KIRK:  Stay seated. Commodore Stocker, I've asked you to be part of this briefing because Gamma Hydra Four falls in your administrative area.</td></tr>

<tr id="L34"><td><a href="#L34">34</a></td><td>STOCKER:  I appreciate that, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L35"><td><a href="#L35">35</a></td><td>KIRK:  Doctor Wallace, as an expert in endocrinology, I'd appreciate you working very closely Doctor McCoy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>WALLACE:  (a young blonde woman in a pink dress) Yes, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>KIRK:  Doctor McCoy, would you fill them in?</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>MCCOY:  The expedition is suffering from extreme old age, and they're growing older by the minute. Much older. My examinations have turned up absolutely nothing. In fact, I don't have a clue.</td></tr>

<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>KIRK:  What about the atmosphere and environment, Mister Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Sensors reveal nothing which is inimical to human life. The atmosphere screens out the usual amount of harmful cosmic rays.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>KIRK:  We're close to the neutral Zone between our Federation and the Romulan empire. It's possible the Romulans have a new weapon and are using this colony as guinea pigs.</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I have already begun investigation into that possibility, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>KIRK:  Good. I want you all to check out everything in your own departments. No matter how remote, how far-fetched the notion, I want it run down. We'll stay in orbit until we have the answer.</td></tr>

<tr id="L44"><td><a href="#L44">44</a></td><td>STOCKER:  I'm sure you understand that I'm anxious to get to Starbase Ten to assume my new post.</td></tr>

<tr id="L45"><td><a href="#L45">45</a></td><td>KIRK:  Yes, Commodore. We'll do everything we can to make sure you make your duty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>STOCKER:  Thank you, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Everyone leaves, but Doctor Wallace remains seated.</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>KIRK:  Doctor, is there something I can do for you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>WALLACE:  Well, be a little less the cool, efficient Captain and a little more the old friend.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>KIRK:  How long has it been?</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>WALLACE:  Six years, four months, and an odd number of days. You mean you don't know?</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, it's been a long time. Things wouldn't change if it started all over again, would it? You have your job, I have my ship, and neither one of us will change.</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>WALLACE:  You said it. I didn't. In all those years, I only heard from you once. A stargram when my husband died. You know, you never asked me why I got married after we called it off.</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, I supposed that you met someone you loved.</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>WALLACE:  I met a man I admired. A great man.</td></tr>

<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>KIRK:  And in your field as you. You didn't give up a thing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>WALLACE:  No. Just you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>UHURA [OC]:  Captain Kirk, Mister Spock would like to see you on the Bridge.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>KIRK:  I'm on my way.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
