<tr id="L106"><td><a href="#L106">106</a></td><td>KIRK:  Scotty!</td></tr>

<tr id="L107"><td><a href="#L107">107</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Captain's log, stardate 3579.4. The Enterprise personnel who beamed down to the planet's surface, Doctor McCoy, Engineer Scott, Mister Spock, Lieutenant Galway, and myself are all showing definite signs of aging. Only Ensign Chekov appears to be normal.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L108"><td><a href="#L108">108</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Chekov is on the stamina machine, Spock is on a bio-bed, Kirk and McCoy are definitely looking older. Chapel and Wallace are also present.</td></tr>

<tr id="L109"><td><a href="#L109">109</a></td><td>KIRK:  Report, Bones.</td></tr>

<tr id="L110"><td><a href="#L110">110</a></td><td>MCCOY:  All of us who went down to the surface, with the exception of Chekov, are aging at various rates. Approximately thirty years for each day. I don't know what's causing it. A virus, a bacteria, or evil spirits, but I'm trying to find out.</td></tr>

<tr id="L111"><td><a href="#L111">111</a></td><td>KIRK:  Spock, could I ask for some figures?</td></tr>

<tr id="L112"><td><a href="#L112">112</a></td><td>SPOCK:  (looking about the same as usual) Based on what Doctor McCoy gave me, I estimate that physically we each have less than a week to live. Also, since our mental faculties are aging faster than our bodies, we will be little better than mental vegetables in considerably lesser time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L113"><td><a href="#L113">113</a></td><td>KIRK:  Total senility?</td></tr>

<tr id="L114"><td><a href="#L114">114</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Yes, Captain. In a very short time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L115"><td><a href="#L115">115</a></td><td>KIRK:  What a way to die. All right. I want all the research facilities, all the scientific technicians, to start round-the-clock research immediately. I want the answers, and I want the remedy. Let's start by finding out why Chekov hasn't been affected.</td></tr>

<tr id="L116"><td><a href="#L116">116</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I'm doing what I can. (to Spock) You're perfectly healthy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L117"><td><a href="#L117">117</a></td><td>SPOCK:  (sitting up) I must differ with you, Doctor. I'm having difficulty concentrating, which is most disturbing, my eye sight appears to be failing, and the normal temperature of the ship seems to me to be increasingly cold.</td></tr>

<tr id="L118"><td><a href="#L118">118</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I did not say you weren't affected, Mister Spock. You are perfectly healthy, that is, for any normal Vulcan on the high side of a hundred.</td></tr>

<tr id="L119"><td><a href="#L119">119</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Captain, can I go back to my station?</td></tr>

<tr id="L120"><td><a href="#L120">120</a></td><td>KIRK:  You feel up to it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L121"><td><a href="#L121">121</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Of course I do. I just need a wee bit of rest, that's all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L122"><td><a href="#L122">122</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He leaves, with Spock giving him a hand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L123"><td><a href="#L123">123</a></td><td>MCCOY:  You can leave, too, Lieutenant Galway. Lieutenant Galway?</td></tr>

<tr id="L124"><td><a href="#L124">124</a></td><td>GALWAY:  What? You spoke to me, Doctor?</td></tr>

<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Yes, I spoke to you. I said that you could leave, too. Now why don't you go down to your quarters and get some sleep.</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>GALWAY:  No. I don't want to sleep. Can't you understand? If I sleep, what will I find when I wake up?</td></tr>

<tr id="L127"><td><a href="#L127">127</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Camera finally pans over to show us an old woman with a dowagers hump.</td></tr>

<tr id="L128"><td><a href="#L128">128</a></td><td>KIRK:  Lieutenant Galway, assume your position. Start your duties.</td></tr>

<tr id="L129"><td><a href="#L129">129</a></td><td>GALWAY:  Thank you, sir. (on her way out) What a stupid place to hang a mirror.</td></tr>

<tr id="L130"><td><a href="#L130">130</a></td><td>KIRK:  She's ten years younger than I am, and she looks,</td></tr>

<tr id="L131"><td><a href="#L131">131</a></td><td>MCCOY:  People age normally at different speeds, Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L132"><td><a href="#L132">132</a></td><td>KIRK:  Why hasn't he aged?</td></tr>

<tr id="L133"><td><a href="#L133">133</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I don't know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well I want to know! Is it his youth, his blood type, his heritage, his glands, his genes?</td></tr>

