<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Corridor</td></tr>
<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Doctor Wallace is waiting for Kirk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>KIRK:  I thought you were on your way to the biochemistry lab, Doctor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>WALLACE:  We both go in the same direction.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>KIRK:  So we do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>WALLACE:  Look, we know the problem. We know the progress of the affliction. Therefore, once we find the proper line of research, it's only logical we find the solution.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>KIRK:  You sound like my first officer.</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>WALLACE:  No problem is insoluble. Not even ours.</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>KIRK:  That didn't spring from logic.</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>WALLACE:  Our situation doesn't have its roots in logic. The heart is not a logical organ. When I married Theodore Wallace, I thought I was over you. I was wrong.</td></tr>

<tr id="L151"><td><a href="#L151">151</a></td><td>KIRK:  When did you realise that? Today?</td></tr>

<tr id="L152"><td><a href="#L152">152</a></td><td>WALLACE:  What?</td></tr>

<tr id="L153"><td><a href="#L153">153</a></td><td>KIRK:  How much older was your husband than you?</td></tr>

